# 3. Critical Decisions & Reasoning History

**Freshness: ✅ High — decisions are reflected in current commit and docs.**

- LangGraph custom StateGraph was chosen over opaque prebuilt orchestration so
  routes, revision budgets, state, and trace are explicit.
- A deterministic offline model and dated demo corpus are the default so the
  project is runnable without keys, credits, or hidden network calls.
- Live mode never falls back to fixtures. Partial live provider failure becomes a
  visible warning if other evidence survives.
- ChromaDB was removed after a no-fixed-version audit finding. SQLite vector memory
  avoids an exposed server and vulnerable transitive set while retaining durable
  semantic recall.
- PyMuPDF was kept for mature PDF parsing, with AGPL licensing disclosed.
- Streamlit was selected for a complete portfolio workbench quickly; custom CSS
  follows a restrained document/research product aesthetic.
- One process-wide UI engine plus an engine run lock preserves a single local
  SQLite writer across Streamlit sessions. API and UI must not run concurrently
  on the same volume.
- arXiv cache misses and requests are serialized so the documented minimum pacing
  survives concurrent callers.
- Prior same-thread PDFs are preserved for follow-up, but old web/arXiv evidence is
  not inserted ahead of fresh sources and allowed to consume the new budget.
- Normal pytest sockets are disabled with Unix IPC allowed. Live and E2E targets
  explicitly opt in.
- Source URLs, prompt payloads, conversation windows, titles, PDFs, upload batches,
  retries, source counts, and revision counts all have enforced bounds.

